On Tuesday, April 11, 2006, at 05:41PM, Richard Atwell <ratwell(-at-)mac.com> wrote:

>After the tie-rods are adjusted to set the proper toe at the wheels, jack up the front wheels and turn the steering wheel all the way left, then counting rotations, all the way right. Then go back half of what you counted and this should center the road wheels.

I think I described this incorrecly.

To get the road wheels straight ahead you need to eyeball it and remember what position to steering wheel likes to reside. Afterwards you can disconnect the draglink and center the steering box with the steering wheel.

